    angular-front end technology
--------basic commands
      -------------------
     1.creation of angular project-ng new project-name
     2.to run angular project-ng serve
     3.component creation-ng g c component-name
     4.service creation-ng g s Service-name


     ----------basic concepts
                --------------
        1.module-to import 3rd party library 

        2.components-html,css,ts

        3.to set up path for component-App routing module file

        4.routing-outlet selector

        5.angular service 

        6.dependency injection - inside constructor

                   syntax:access-specifier object-name:dependent class name

        7.asynchronous - rxjs - observable - subscribe()

        8.data binding- sharing data inside a component
             
             1.one way Binding-

                1.component to view

                   1.string interpolation - {{variable - name}}
                   2.property binding - [attribute]="property-name"

                2.view to component

                  1.event binding - (event)="function-call"
                  2.event binding using $event - (event)="funcyion-call($event)
                  3.template reference variable,#variable-name


              3.two way binding
              1.ngModel (tmplate driven forms)
                -import formsModule,, [(ngModel)]="variable-name"

        9.angular directive - to manipulate DOM
           
            1.component directive

            2.structural directive - to add/remove html elements

                1. *ngIf="condition"
                2. *ngFor="let variable-name of array-name"

        10.ActivatedRoute - provide access to information about a route 
        asssociated with a component

        11.router class-

        12.pipe-